```json
{
  "application": "obsproc",
  "details": {
    "software": {
      "obsproc": "v1.1.2",
      "prepobs": "1.0.0",
      "grib_util": "${grib_util_ver}",
      "netcdf": "${netcdf_ver}",
      "bufr_dump": "${bufr_dump_ver}",
      "intel": "${intel_ver}",
      "craype": "${craype_ver}",
      "cray-mpich": "${cray_mpich_ver}",
      "cray-pals": "${cray_pals_ver}",
      "cfp": "${cfp_ver}"
    },
    "resource_requirements": {
      "walltime": "00:05:00",
      "memory": "1gb",
      "cpus": 1,
      "queue": "dev",
      "account": "OBSPROC-DEV"
    },
    "environment_variables": {
      "envir": "prod",
      "cyc": "%CC%",
      "DESC": "%DESC%",
      "JTYP": "%JTYP%",
      "job": "${JTYP}_prep_post_$cyc",
      "PDY": "%PDY%",
      "obsNET": "obsproc",
      "obsproc_ver": "v1.1",
      "obsproc_ver_pckg": "v1.1.2",
      "prepobs_ver": "1.0.0",
      "PACKAGEROOTpara": "/lfs/h1/ops/para/packages",
      "HOMEobsproc": "${userROOT}/install/obsproc-rel.v1.0.0",
      "VERSION_FILE": "${HOMEobsproc}/versions/run.ver",
      "SENDECF": "NO",
      "SENDDBN": "NO",
      "SENDSDM": "NO",
      "DATAROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/$USER",
      "jlogfile": "/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/$USER/${JTYP}.$PDY.jlogfile",
      "COMIN_ROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/$USER/CRON/${DESC}/com",
      "COMOUT_ROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/stmp/$USER/CRON/${DESC}/com",
      "DEBUG_LEVEL": 3,
      "KEEPDATA": "YES",
      "LOUD": "ON"
    },
    "data_paths": {
      "userROOT": "/lfs/h2/emc/obsproc/noscrub/$USER"
    },
    "executable": "$HOMEobsproc/jobs/JOBSPROC_GLOBAL_PREP_POST"
  }
}
```

This script is running an **obsproc** application. It uses various software packages for data processing, including obsproc itself, prepobs, grib_util, netcdf, bufr_dump, intel, craype, cray-mpich, cray-pals, and cfp. The script sets up several environment variables and defines data paths. It utilizes a PBS queue system, requesting resources such as walltime, memory, and CPUs. It also defines specific environment variables for different processes. Finally, it executes the $HOMEobsproc/jobs/JOBSPROC_GLOBAL_PREP_POST script for data processing.
